```sql
-- Create index
CREATE INDEX idx_name ON table(column);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_email ON users(email);
CREATE INDEX idx_composite ON table(col1, col2);

-- Drop index
DROP INDEX idx_name ON table;
```
Indexes speed up data retrieval at the cost of additional storage and slower writes. Essential for columns used in WHERE, JOIN, and ORDER BY.

```sql
BEGIN TRANSACTION;
  -- SQL statements
  INSERT INTO ...
  UPDATE ...
COMMIT;

-- On error:
ROLLBACK;

-- With savepoints:
BEGIN;
  SAVEPOINT sp1;
  -- statements
  ROLLBACK TO sp1;
COMMIT;
```
Starts a transaction. All subsequent operations are grouped and applied atomically with COMMIT, or undone with ROLLBACK.

```sql
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = 'test@example.com';

-- With actual execution stats (PostgreSQL)
EXPLAIN ANALYZE SELECT ...;

-- MySQL extended
EXPLAIN FORMAT=JSON SELECT ...;
```
Displays the query execution plan chosen by the database optimizer. Shows index usage, join strategies, and estimated row counts. Essential for query performance tuning.

```sql
-- Grant specific privileges
GRANT SELECT, INSERT ON database.table TO 'user'@'host';

-- Grant all privileges
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON database.* TO 'user'@'host';

-- Allow user to grant to others
GRANT SELECT ON table TO user WITH GRANT OPTION;
```
Grants access privileges on database objects to users or roles.
